reviewText: This DVD is pure pleasure. It makes you wonder how such a talented artist could not maintain her huge popularity through the years. Her voice is in pristine shape and the notes she hits are mind-blowing. The piece is made even more wonderful by the addition of the dancers who are trying to recreate the dances and the era in which Martha made all those songs megasmashes. One downside is that I was led to believe that Martha duets with Sam Cooke on some of his smashes since this is her DVD and her moment to shine. What better way than to have her due with Sam on some of his classics?
summary: Martha as you've never seen her before

reviewText: This is simply Mickey Gilley and his Urban Cowboy Band, including Joe Riley, along with the Urbanettes (2 beautiful lady backup singers), at their very best. This was filmed before Mickey fell off a porch, while moving furniture. He was down for about a year, but around April 2010, he made a "comeback", and started performing again. I saw him and his Urban Cowboy Band perform a Live Concert, down in his home Parish of Concordia, Louisiana, in September, 2010. It was great. This is one great Concert DVD. Since the amazon product description does not give the song set, then I will.The songs include:1.I'm the one Mama Warned You About2.True Love Ways (a Buddy Holly song)3.Talk to Me4.Put Your Dreams Away5.That's All that Matters to Me6.Don't the Girls All Get Prettier At Closing Time7.You Don't Know Me8.I Didn't Know Your Memory Loved Jamaica9.A Headache Tomorrow or a Heartache Tonight10.Band Instrumental11.Medley: Room Full of Roses, I Over looked an Orchid, Window Up Above.12.Great Balls of Fire13.Back in the Doo-Wah Days14.Honkey Tonk Wine15.Here Comes that Hurt Again16.Cherokee Fiddle17.Lookin' for Love (from the Urban Cowboy Movie)18.Stand by Me19.Diggy Liggy LoPlus, you get a bonus interview with Mickey Gilley. If you like Mickey Gilley, you will not be disappointed in this one, for sure. This is a great one, and I highly recommend it. Thanks!!!!
summary: Mickey Gilley & his Urban Cowboy Band, At Their Best. This was filmed at his Branson Theatre, before Mickey's injury.
